
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the "username" argument does not exist in the [.arguments] node. If it doesn't exist, it adds a new node with the name "username" and the value "root" to the [.arguments] node. The [if] slot is used for conditional execution, the [not] slot inverts the condition, and the [exists] slot checks for the presence of the "username" node.
if
   not
      exists:x:@.arguments/*/username
   .lambda
      add:x:@.arguments
         .
            username:root
